.TH btctax-reconcile-classify-inbound-income 1  btctax "btctax manual"
.SH NAME
classify\-inbound\-income \- Classify an inbound TransferIn as income
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBclassify\-inbound\-income\fR <\fB\-\-kind\fR> [\fB\-\-fmv\fR] [\fB\-\-business\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIIN_REF\fR> 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Classify an inbound TransferIn as income
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-kind\fR \fI<KIND>\fR
Income kind: one of `mining`, `staking`, `interest`, `airdrop`, `reward`
.TP
\fB\-\-fmv\fR \fI<FMV>\fR
Fair\-market value of the received BTC at receipt — USD dollars, NOT sats. On this single\-event command there is NO auto\-valuation: omitting `\-\-fmv` records a Hard "FMV missing" blocker (re\-classify with `\-\-fmv` to clear it). To value automatically from the bundled daily close, use `reconcile bulk\-classify\-inbound\-income` instead
.TP
\fB\-\-business\fR
Mark this income as earned in a trade or business (routes to Schedule C / SE tax)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
<\fIIN_REF\fR>
The inbound TransferIn event reference to classify (see `btctax events list`)
